# ⚠️ SECURITY WARNING ⚠️
# Chronos MCP stores credentials in PLAIN TEXT at ~/.chronos/accounts.json
# Only use on trusted systems with proper file permissions!
# See SECURITY.md for details and mitigation strategies

# Example environment configuration for Chronos MCP
# Copy this to .env and update with your CalDAV server details

# Default CalDAV account (for backward compatibility)
CALDAV_BASE_URL=http://your-caldav-server.com:5232
CALDAV_USERNAME=your_username
CALDAV_PASSWORD=your_password

# For multiple accounts, use ~/.chronos/accounts.json instead
